.TH "nfs_verify_change_attribute" 9 "nfs_verify_change_attribute" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nfs_verify_change_attribute \- Detects NFS remote directory changes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" nfs_verify_change_attribute
.BI "(struct inode *dir "  ","
.BI "unsigned long verf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dir" 12
pointer to parent directory inode
.IP "verf" 12
previously saved change attribute
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return "false" if the verifiers doesn't match the change attribute.
This would usually indicate that the directory contents have changed on
the server, and that any dentries need revalidating.
